The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, Jan. 17: Three youths, who were to sit for their HS exams this year, have been arrested for a series of robberies in Barasat and Madhyamgram.     
	In all, five, aged between 18 and 20, were caught. Of them, two are brothers  Ripon and Liton Thakur. The HS examinees are Moloy Debnath, Suman Saha and Santu Mondal, said a police officer.         
	Calcutta: A worker of a plastic goods manufacturing unit was beaten to death by his colleagues on Friday night. Police said the alleged murder was a fallout of a fight between the worker Hiralal Kumar, from Madhubani in Bihar, and three others.         
	Chinsurah: Four youths last night shot at a taxi driver when he asked for the fare. Police said the youths had hired the cab from Howrah station and asked Mohammed Hasir, 40, to take them to Hind Motor. After reaching their destination, the youths refused to pay and one of them fired at Hasir, injuring him.                                                                                                                                                                       
